{"/service/ndnp/mohi/batch_mohi_beetlebailey_ver01/data/sn88068010/00294556102/1908011701/0183.xml":{"full_text":"1\nA Great Reduced Price Sale for\nw\nfE are going to offer the people of KEYTESVILLE AND CHARITON COUNTY a Great Opportunity\nto Save Money on Dependable Merchandise, Last fall we bought much heavier than usual, the warm\nweather which we have had and the brief financial panic causes us to be overstocked for this season of the\nyear, In order to meet our obligations we have got to have money and, in order to get money, we are offer\ning'everything in this stock at Greatly Reduced Prices in some cases less than the goods cost us laid down at\nKeytesville depot. This is no hot air talk,but a straight business proposition and a call at our store will convince\nyou that we are doing just what we say we are.\nAW\nmm\nu cH3g\nENDING SATURDAY, FEBRUARY 1, 1908,\nWe will offer for sale every article of merchandise in this store at prices you cannot match anywhere. Nothing will be reserved, but the knife has gone into the\nprice of every article we carry. Wc pledge you our word tuat not one article of bankrupt stock has been brought in for this sale, but it is just what we claim it\nto be a genuine, bona fide, cut-price sale in order to reduce our stock and meet our bills. Another feature of this sale to which we must call attention is that it is\nfor spot cash. Nothing will be allowed to go out of the store until it is paid for, for we could not afford to sell goods at these prices and charge them, besides\nthe purpose of this sale is to raise ready money.\nAs a hint to show how we ore cutting prices throughout the store, see the following:\nDress Goods\nAll 1.25 Dress Goods,\nAll 1.00\nAll .75\nAll .50 44\na\nnow .87\n.75\n.50\n.38J\nMen's Dress Shirts\nAll 1.00 Dress Shirts,\nAll ,75\nAH ,50 44\nnow .75\n.50\n.40\nShoes\nMen's 5.00 Crossett Shoes,\n3.50\n3.00 5\n2.50\n2.00\nnow $3.75\n44 3.25\n2.90\n44 2.35\n2.00\n44 1.75\nHats\nAll 3.00 Thoroughbred Hats,\nAll 2.50\nAll 2.00\nAll 1.50\n4(\nnow $2.25\n1.75\n1.50\n1.15\na\na\na\nWool Blankets\nAll-wool 11-4 7.00 Blankets,\nAll-wool 11-4 6.00\nAll-wool 11-4 5.00\nAll-wool 104 4.50\na\nnow $5,50\n4.50\n4.00\n3.35\n1\nUnderwear\nAll 1.00 Garments,\nAll .75\nAll .50\nnow .75\n.50\n44 .38\nThe above is just a sample of the way prices are cut on everything in the store. Nothing is held in reserve. We are not making leaders of anything, but are genuinely\ncutting prices throughout the stock. The warm weather has left us with a great deal too much stock on our hands and it must be turned into cash just as quickly as\npossible. In many instances you can buy these goods eheaper than we could buy them from the wholesale houses.\nH Elo\nIT V?\nJ U Ul J Ul J 1A\nC0o\nKEY\nVILL\nMO\nBear this in mind: This Sale is for Spot Cash.\nRemember the date:\ntarasir I Mb til MbrawY I\n111- imJJ V 1 I 1 XV mM i mmw mm m-m m\nrnmmm","height":"33244","width":"24108"}}
